/// note:
/// Values provided here act as defaults for a button configuration and can be
/// overridden where appropriate. Prefer using <code>APButtonStyleType</code> for standard appearances.
/// Properties:
/// <ul>
///   <li>
///     <code>containerColor</code>: Background color for the button when enabled.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     <code>containerInactiveColor</code>: Background color for the button when disabled.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     <code>borderColor</code>: Border color for the button when enabled.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     <code>borderInactiveColor</code>: Border color for the button when disabled.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     <code>textStyle</code>: Text style (font and color) for the enabled state.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     <code>textInactiveStyle</code>: Text style (font and color) for the disabled state.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     <code>iconColor</code>: Optional tint color for any icon displayed in the button.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     <code>cornerRadius</code>: Corner radius applied to the button’s container. Use <code>.infinity</code> for a pill shape.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     <code>borderWidth</code>: Width of the button’s border, in points.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     <code>minHeight</code>: Minimum height of the button, in points.
///   </li>
/// </ul>
/// Example:
/// <ul>
///   <li>
///     Use <code>.init(style: .primary)</code> for high-emphasis actions.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     Increase <code>cornerRadius</code> or set to <code>.infinity</code> for pill-shaped buttons.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     Adjust <code>borderWidth</code> and <code>borderColor</code> for outlined buttons.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     Provide distinct <code>textInactiveStyle</code> and <code>containerInactiveColor</code> to clarify disabled states.
///   </li>
/// </ul>
/// Thread-safety:
/// <ul>
///   <li>
///     This type is a simple configuration object and is not thread-safe by design.
///     Configure it on the main thread or before passing it to UI components.
///   </li>
/// </ul>
/// Accessibility:
/// <ul>
///   <li>
///     Ensure sufficient contrast between text and background in both enabled and disabled states.
///   </li>
///   <li>
///     Consider larger <code>minHeight</code> values to improve tap targets and ergonomics.
///   </li>
/// </ul>
